<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="259" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1301,1758]" pageId="7" pageNumber="259">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1337,1362]" pageId="7" pageNumber="259">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Small to minute shells. Equivalve. Equilateral to slightly inequilateral with prosogyrous beaks posterior of the midline. Outline transversely ovate to subcircular, posterior area weakly demarcated by a radial angulation; submarginal sulcus long and shallow; lunule a slight depression. Hinge with an anterior tubercle or thickening that in the right valve most developed. Exteriorly most with a heavy ferruginous coating. Ctenidium of a single demibranch, foot with a developed heel, lateral body pouches with few branches.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="259" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1301,1758]" pageId="7" pageNumber="259">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1517,1542]" pageId="7" pageNumber="259">Remarks.</emphasis>
The above diagnosis is somewhat more restrictive than that given by 
<bibRefCitation author="Payne" box="[1129,1385,1517,1542]" pageId="7" pageNumber="259" refString="Payne, C. M. &amp; Allen, J. A. (1991) The morphology of deep-sea Thyasiridae (Mollusca: Bivalvia) from the Atlantic Ocean. Philosophical Transactions of the Royal Society of London Series B, 334, 481 - 566. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1098 / rstb. 1991.0128" type="journal article" year="1991">
Payne &amp; Allen (
<number box="[1319,1377,1518,1542]" pageId="7" pageNumber="259" value="1991.0">1991</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and would exclude species such as 
<taxonomicName authority="Payne &amp; Allen, 1991" authorityName="Payne &amp; Allen" authorityYear="1991" box="[505,1018,1553,1578]" class="Bivalvia" family="Thyasiridae" genus="Thyasira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lucinoida" pageId="7" pageNumber="259" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="carrozae" subGenus="M.">
<emphasis box="[505,605,1553,1578]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="259">Thyasira</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[622,645,1554,1577]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="259">M</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[670,768,1554,1577]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="259">carrozae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Payne" box="[778,1018,1553,1578]" pageId="7" pageNumber="259" refString="Payne, C. M. &amp; Allen, J. A. (1991) The morphology of deep-sea Thyasiridae (Mollusca: Bivalvia) from the Atlantic Ocean. Philosophical Transactions of the Royal Society of London Series B, 334, 481 - 566. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1098 / rstb. 1991.0128" type="journal article" year="1991">
Payne &amp; Allen, 
<number box="[962,1018,1554,1578]" pageId="7" pageNumber="259" value="1991.0">1991</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
where there is a well developed peg like tooth in each valve; 
<taxonomicName authority="Payne &amp; Allen, 1991" authorityName="Payne &amp; Allen" authorityYear="1991" box="[423,818,1589,1614]" class="Bivalvia" family="Thyasiridae" genus="Thyasira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lucinoida" pageId="7" pageNumber="259" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="ultima" subGenus="M.">
<emphasis box="[423,436,1590,1613]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="259">T</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis box="[460,483,1590,1613]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="259">M</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[505,577,1589,1614]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="259">ultima</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Payne" box="[583,818,1589,1614]" pageId="7" pageNumber="259" refString="Payne, C. M. &amp; Allen, J. A. (1991) The morphology of deep-sea Thyasiridae (Mollusca: Bivalvia) from the Atlantic Ocean. Philosophical Transactions of the Royal Society of London Series B, 334, 481 - 566. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1098 / rstb. 1991.0128" type="journal article" year="1991">
Payne &amp; Allen, 
<quantity box="[762,818,1590,1614]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.05714" pageId="7" pageNumber="259" unit="in" value="1991.0">1991</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in which there are well developed myophoric ridges on both adductor scars and 
<taxonomicName authority="Payne &amp; Allen, 1991" authorityName="Payne &amp; Allen" authorityYear="1991" box="[424,830,1625,1650]" class="Bivalvia" family="Thyasiridae" genus="Thyasira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lucinoida" pageId="7" pageNumber="259" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="verrilli" subGenus="M.">
<emphasis box="[424,438,1626,1649]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="259">T</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis box="[461,484,1626,1649]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="259">M</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[508,586,1625,1650]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="259">verrilli</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Payne" box="[593,830,1625,1650]" pageId="7" pageNumber="259" refString="Payne, C. M. &amp; Allen, J. A. (1991) The morphology of deep-sea Thyasiridae (Mollusca: Bivalvia) from the Atlantic Ocean. Philosophical Transactions of the Royal Society of London Series B, 334, 481 - 566. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1098 / rstb. 1991.0128" type="journal article" year="1991">
Payne &amp; Allen, 
<number box="[774,830,1626,1650]" pageId="7" pageNumber="259" value="1991.0">1991</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
where there are weak myophoric lines. These species are anatomically similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[458,578,1661,1686]" class="Bivalvia" family="Thyasiridae" genus="Mendicula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lucinoida" pageId="7" pageNumber="259" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[458,578,1661,1686]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="259">Mendicula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and cannot be transferred to 
<taxonomicName box="[906,1006,1661,1686]" class="Bivalvia" family="Thyasiridae" genus="Thyasira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lucinoida" pageId="7" pageNumber="259" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[906,1006,1661,1686]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="259">Thyasira</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Payne" box="[1019,1268,1661,1686]" pageId="7" pageNumber="259" refString="Payne, C. M. &amp; Allen, J. A. (1991) The morphology of deep-sea Thyasiridae (Mollusca: Bivalvia) from the Atlantic Ocean. Philosophical Transactions of the Royal Society of London Series B, 334, 481 - 566. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1098 / rstb. 1991.0128" type="journal article" year="1991">
Payne &amp; Allen (
<number box="[1202,1260,1662,1686]" pageId="7" pageNumber="259" value="1991.0">1991</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
do not include 
<taxonomicName box="[151,292,1697,1722]" class="Bivalvia" family="Thyasiridae" genus="Adontorhina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lucinoida" pageId="7" pageNumber="259" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,292,1697,1722]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="259">Adontorhina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but their 
<taxonomicName authority="Payne &amp; Allen, 1991" authorityName="Payne &amp; Allen" authorityYear="1991" box="[399,844,1697,1722]" class="Bivalvia" family="Thyasiridae" genus="Thyasira" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lucinoida" pageId="7" pageNumber="259" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="transversa" subGenus="M.">
<emphasis box="[399,601,1698,1721]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="259">T. (M.) transversa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Payne" box="[608,844,1697,1722]" pageId="7" pageNumber="259" refString="Payne, C. M. &amp; Allen, J. A. (1991) The morphology of deep-sea Thyasiridae (Mollusca: Bivalvia) from the Atlantic Ocean. Philosophical Transactions of the Royal Society of London Series B, 334, 481 - 566. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1098 / rstb. 1991.0128" type="journal article" year="1991">
Payne &amp; Allen, 
<number box="[788,844,1698,1722]" pageId="7" pageNumber="259" value="1991.0">1991</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
should be transferred to this genus as the hinge plate has microscopic crenulations characteristic of that genus (pers. obs.)
</paragraph>
